		<div id="post-4269" class="cf post-4269 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-uncategorized">

			<h1>
				<a href="http://werblog.com/2013/02/twitter-updates-2013-02-15-to-2013-02-21/" title="Twitter Updates: 2013-02-15 to 2013-02-21" rel="bookmark">Twitter Updates: 2013-02-15 to 2013-02-21</a>
				
			</h1>

			<div class="post-footer">
				22 Feb 2013 &nbsp;&nbsp;| <a href="http://werblog.com/category/uncategorized/">Uncategorized</a>
				
			</div>

			<div class="post-bodycopy cf">
				<ul class="ws_tweet_list">
<li class="ws_tweet">Skype now handles 1/3 as many international call minutes as all the world&#039;s phone companies combined: <a href="http://t.co/Sx81PLmD" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/Sx81PLmD</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/302411617793105922">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Gratz to my RIT friends for the amazing new MAGIC lab on games, media &amp; creativity! <a href="http://t.co/96N8fhlW" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/96N8fhlW</a> <a href="http://twitter.com/mamamusings">@mamamusings</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/302439937884712960">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Considering launching a global crusade to replace <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23TGIF">#TGIF</a> with <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23HSIF">#HSIF</a> (Holy&#8230;). Who&#039;s with me? <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/302455861941514241">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Is it more surprising that few critics of massive online courses (MOOCs) have ever taught one, or that few MOOC proponents have? <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/302861101681487872">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">My Wharton colleague <a href="http://twitter.com/terwiesch">@terwiesch</a> thoughtfully explains Coursera using concepts from operations management: <a href="http://t.co/OmTyk6A8" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/OmTyk6A8</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/302873218581139457">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">As if the health and ethical considerations weren&#039;t enough reason to cut down on meat consumption: <a href="http://t.co/IIHSfk7Z" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/IIHSfk7Z</a> h/t <a href="http://twitter.com/jowyang">@jowyang</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/303498839363555328">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Interesting project. We need more real-world spectrum data! RT <a href="http://twitter.com/przemyslawp">@przemyslawp</a>: Spectrum Observatory from <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23MSR">#MSR</a>. Neat. <a href="http://t.co/OBhn1EOz" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/OBhn1EOz</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/303499430106112001">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">UC Irvine prof leading a Coursera MOOC is replaced amid disagreements. (Comments on this piece are fascinating.) <a href="https://t.co/bntJairB" rel="nofollow">https://t.co/bntJairB</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/303528027646734336">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">My brother <a href="http://twitter.com/adamwerbach">@adamwerbach</a>&#039;s collaborative consumption startup Yerdle launches in NYC on Thursday evening: <a href="http://t.co/GiQYJugP" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/GiQYJugP</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/303624372827082755">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">What would a massively multiplayer online course (MMOC) look like? Or a Massive open online game (MOOG)? Well, the latter is an old synth. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/303624728336269313">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Highly recommended.  RT <a href="http://twitter.com/lessig">@lessig</a>: on preparing for &quot;Aaron&#039;s Laws&quot;: <a href="http://t.co/9oBEPTyY" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/9oBEPTyY</a> <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23aaronswarz">#aaronswarz</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/303630319356104704">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Good the NY Times is raising questions on online education. But wrong to view MOOCs as just more of what came before. <a href="http://t.co/BqlCKQru" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/BqlCKQru</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/304001701172625408">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">We interrupt this Twitter feed for a special message to dynamic, spiritual Jews in Philadelphia: go to this event! <a href="http://t.co/ymX2NdDh5T" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/ymX2NdDh5T</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/304345020029337600">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Fascinating discussing ethics of investment banking with 1st year MBA students. Glad they aren&#039;t the amoral monsters I sometimes read about. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/304379470238842880">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">A: calling everyone who registers for free &amp; doesn&#039;t get a certificate a &quot;dropout.&quot;  RT <a href="http://twitter.com/ddt">@ddt</a>: What drives 90% dropout rate of <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23MOOC">#MOOC</a> courses? <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/304381478089924608">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">True dat. What data should we collect? RT <a href="http://twitter.com/NeilCromby">@NeilCromby</a>: The data being created from MOOC learning is going to be fascinating. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/304385300828917760">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Excellent challenge from this morning&#039;s minyan: compare relationship status and profile options on Facebook, J-Date, and Christian Mingle. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/304387517531172865">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Another wave of MOOC network expansion. Just think what the numbers will be in 3 years.<br />
  <a href="http://t.co/O5r5GP0kKT" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/O5r5GP0kKT</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/304576925114982400">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Thanks <a href="http://twitter.com/selenakyle">@selenakyle</a> for stopping by to talk gamification, MOOCs, and infosec!  Other Wharton alums, don&#039;t be strangers. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/304616595781713921">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">As I prepare for my next session, I&#039;d love to hear your creative ideas to improve the MOOC experience. Use hashtag <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23gamification13">#gamification13</a>. <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/304634691825303552">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">RT <a href="http://twitter.com/whartonmagazine">@whartonmagazine</a>: On the blog: Prof. Kevin Werbach explains <a href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23gamification">#gamification</a> is actually an old business technique. <a href="http://t.co/w26WpQsu5k" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/w26WpQsu5k</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/304656080657588224">-&gt;</a></li>
<li class="ws_tweet">Hmm. Clay Christiansen says universities investing in MOOCs b/c their leaders are now familiar with his theories. <a href="http://t.co/lA3lMBWt8Q" rel="nofollow">http://t.co/lA3lMBWt8Q</a> <a class="ws_tweet_time" href="http://twitter.com/kwerb/statuses/304816970946203648">-&gt;</a></li>
</ul>

				
			</div>

			
			


